events.plain_body:
Lyne,
&nbsp;
You can use a public CA-signed or Enterprise CA-signed certificate for the Fleet Manager WebUI by configuring the ssl-certificate-path and ssl-key-path fields in /etc/corelight-fleetd.conf to point to your custom certificate and key. &nbsp;However, the corelight-fleetd.pem identity certificate (provided by Corelight) must still be used for sensor-to-Fleet Manager communication and licensing; this cannot be replaced with a public/private CA certificate (certificate-path / key-path fields in /etc/corelight-fleetd.conf ).&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Reference:
https://docs.corelight.cloud/fleet/installation/fleet-host-install.html#use-a-tls-certificate-with-fm
&nbsp;
Our license records do show that your current Fleet Manager license does expire on 6/9/2026, which coincides with the error messages in your screenshot. &nbsp; If a license renewal is currently being processed, you will receive the new Fleet Manager license certificate once the renewal process has completed. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
&nbsp;
We can set up a call to discuss further. &nbsp;Please provide a few dates and times when you are available and I will arrange a meeting.
&nbsp;
Thank you,


  Michael Hawks

Senior Escalation Engineer

Corelight 
