events.plain_body:
Hi Jacob,
&nbsp;
Thank you for the update, and I apologise for the inconvenience you've been experiencing with this.
&nbsp;
Could you please perform the following offline update procedure for both of these sensors:
  f1-20-a7-22-c8-c0-b8-f2  36-ad-d2-2b-d0-26-3c-b5  
Firstly, please download the 29.4.5 release image: https://support.corelight.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052242794-How-to-download-and-upgrade-offline-Sensor-versions
  After validating the SHA-256 checksum, transfer the update image file to the offline_updater folder on the sensor. Example scp &lt;filename&gt;.dat diag-shell@&lt;sensor_ip&gt;.:~/offline_updater  SSH into the sensor.  Run the following command first to temporarily disconnect it from Fleet Manager: corelight-client configuration update --fleet.enable="False"  Mount the Image: corelight-updater mount /home/diag-shell/offline_updater/&lt;filename&gt;.dat  Apply the Update: corelight-client updates apply  Clean Up: Once the update is fully completed, unmount and remove the image file from the sensor: corelight-updater unmount and rm /home/diag-shell/offline_updater/&lt;filename&gt;.dat  Reconnect to Fleet Manager: Finally, re-add the sensor to Fleet using: corelight-client configuration update --fleet.enable="True"  &nbsp;
Please let me know if the above steps are clear. I'd be more than happy to jump on a session to walk through this together if needed.
&nbsp;
Thanks,&nbsp;
Travis Anderson

